section.def:
appellant
                (上訴人) means the party appealing under Part VII
            from a decision of a magistrate;

fine
                (罰款) includes any pecuniary penalty or pecuniary
            forfeiture or pecuniary compensation payable under a conviction or order;

subparagraph.content:
issue a warrant for the arrest of the defendant;
                        (See
                            Form 2)

paragraph.content:
grant such adjournment as may be reasonably necessary to
                                        enable the parties to call or recall witnesses and to
                                        prepare their cases;

section.def:
juvenile
                (少年) means a person who is, in the opinion of the
            magistrate presiding at the committal proceedings, under the age of 16 years;

paragraph.content:
where the accused pleads guilty in proceedings under section
                    80C, require the prosecutor to outline to the accused, to the satisfaction
                    of the magistrate, the alleged facts upon which the charge is based;

content.proviso:
Provided that he may admit
                        the accused to bail in any case where he has power to grant bail under the
                        provisions of this Ordinance;

paragraph.content:
any decision of the magistrate to commit the accused for trial, and any
                    decision of the magistrate on the disposal of the case of any defendants not
                    committed;

where the magistrate commits the accused for trial, the charge, or a
                    summary thereof, on which he is committed and the court to which he is
                    committed;

in the case of publication of a written report as part of a newspaper or
                    periodical publication, any proprietor, editor, publisher or distributor
                    thereof;

in the case of a publication of a written report otherwise than as part of
                    a newspaper or periodical publication, the person who publishes or distributes
                    it;

subparagraph.content:
an order for payment of compensation;
                        (Replaced 36 of 1976 s.
                        14)
